article.headline: Tenn.-Martin 87, Austin Peay 82
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Lester Hudson scored all of Tennessee-Martin's points in the final 3 minutes of regulation and added six in overtime to help sink Austin Peay 87-82 on Thursday night. The Skyhawks (15-6, 8-3 Ohio Valley Conference) trailed the Governors (12-10, 8-4) by four points at halftime. The teams would trade leads until Austin Peay scored six points in one minute, giving the Governors a 61-54 lead with 5:51 left. Hudson hit two free throws to cap an 8-0 run from that point, hit a 3-pointer less than two minutes later and nailed both foul shots in the final seconds to send the game into overtime tied at 67. Hudson hit three free throws and a 3-pointer in overtime, helping the Skyhawks outscore the Governors 20-15 in the extra period. Hudson finished with 30 points and 10 boards. Drake Reed scored 35 points and had 18 rebounds for the Governors.
